device.contactinfo: Kueferstrasse 16 D-59067 Hamm Germany support@microsens.de http://www.microsens.de
device.description: Microsens private MIB for Generation 6 Ethernet Switches

hardwareLedTest.name: hardwareLedTest
hardwareLedTest.description: Runs a leds test whereby all LED light up in all possible colors for checking their function. The tests terminates within a few seconds.

hardwareLedMode.name: hardwareLedMode
hardwareLedMode.description: The LED display can be configured to be less intrusive.

hardwarePowerSupply1Monitored.name: hardwarePowerSupply1Monitored
hardwarePowerSupply1Monitored.description: When disabled a missing power supply 1 will not turn the associated led red on failure. Do this when single power supply 2 operation is used or when the device is powered soley by PoE. This feature only applies to industrial switches.

hardwarePowerSupply2Monitored.name: hardwarePowerSupply2Monitored
hardwarePowerSupply2Monitored.description: When disabled a missing power supply 2 will not turn the associated led red on failure. Do this when single power supply 1 operation is used or when the device is powered soley by PoE. This feature only applies to industrial switches.

hardwareFactoryResetButton.name: hardwareFactoryResetButton
hardwareFactoryResetButton.description: When disabled the factory button will trigger the factory reset function when pressed for a long time. The IP discover function upon a short button click is not affected.

cableTestConfigTable.name: cableTestConfigTable
cableTestConfigTable.description: The cable tester allows for detection of copper cable faults and can even detect where the fault is located.

cableTestConfigEnableAutoCableTest.name: cableTestConfigEnableAutoCableTest
cableTestConfigEnableAutoCableTest.description: When enabled a cable test is performed each time the link goes down. The test is only performed for copper ports or dual media ports in copper mode.

cableTestConfigEventGeneration.name: cableTestConfigEventGeneration
cableTestConfigEventGeneration.description: When the cable termination status changes an event can be raised.

cableTestConfigStartTestNow.name: cableTestConfigStartTestNow
cableTestConfigStartTestNow.description: May be used to manually start a cable test. ATTENTION: If the port is in link up status it will be forced to link down first. This will disrupt the current data traffic. Therefore, type start_test_now = CONFIRM.

ioSignalConfigSignalMode.name: ioSignalConfigSignalMode
ioSignalConfigSignalMode.description: Permit setting of io signal LEDs and relays to static or blink blink mode for increased visualization.

ioSignalConfigInput1Mode.name: ioSignalConfigInput1Mode
ioSignalConfigInput1Mode.description: When this function is activated the external alarm input 1 is monitored. Note: alarm inputs are not available in all product versions.

ioSignalConfigInput1Name.name: ioSignalConfigInput1Name
ioSignalConfigInput1Name.description: A customer specific name can be specified for input 1. This name will appear in the associated event messages.

ioSignalConfigInput2Mode.name: ioSignalConfigInput2Mode
ioSignalConfigInput2Mode.description: When this function is activated the external alarm input 2 is monitored. Note: alarm inputs are not available in all product versions.

ioSignalConfigInput2Name.name: ioSignalConfigInput2Name
ioSignalConfigInput2Name.description: A customer specific name can be specified for input 2. This name will appear in the associated event messages.

ioSignalConfigOutput1Trigger.name: ioSignalConfigOutput1Trigger
ioSignalConfigOutput1Trigger.description: Defines on which condition the alarm relay 1 is activated. Note: alarm relays are not available in all product versions.

ioSignalConfigOutput1Name.name: ioSignalConfigOutput1Name
ioSignalConfigOutput1Name.description: A customer specific name can be specified for alarm output 1. This name will appear in the associated event messages.

ioSignalConfigOutput2Trigger.name: ioSignalConfigOutput2Trigger
ioSignalConfigOutput2Trigger.description: Defines on which condition the alarm relay 2 is activated. Note: alarm relays are not available in all product versions.

ioSignalConfigOutput2Name.name: ioSignalConfigOutput2Name
ioSignalConfigOutput2Name.description: A customer specific name can be specified for alarm output 2. This name will appear in the associated event messages.

hardwarePowerSupply1Status.name: hardwarePowerSupply1Status
hardwarePowerSupply1Status.description: Displays state of primary supply or only supply for single supply systems.

hardwarePowerSupply2Status.name: hardwarePowerSupply2Status
hardwarePowerSupply2Status.description: Displays state of secondary supply if available.

hardwareRunningOnPoe.name: hardwareRunningOnPoe
hardwareRunningOnPoe.description: When set the unit currently operates on the PD input via PoE.

hardwareFanStatus.name: hardwareFanStatus
hardwareFanStatus.description: Displays state of cooling fan. Indicates UNUSED in fanless devices.

hardwareNumOfPorts.name: hardwareNumOfPorts
hardwareNumOfPorts.description: Total number of Ethernet ports this hardware offers.

hardwareMaskOfExistingPorts.name: hardwareMaskOfExistingPorts
hardwareMaskOfExistingPorts.description: Set bit for each port that physically exisiting and could be in use.

hardwareMaskOfPoePorts.name: hardwareMaskOfPoePorts
hardwareMaskOfPoePorts.description: Marks which ports support PoE output.

cableTestStatusTable.name: cableTestStatusTable
cableTestStatusTable.description: This table display the result of the last cable test. Values are only available for copper ports while a link is down and if the cable test function is enabled.

cableTestStatusUpdateTimeStamp.description: Indicates the time when this record was last updated.

cableTestStatusPair0State.description: Indicates line termination test results for wire pair 0 (Pins 1/2)

cableTestStatusPair0DistanceToFault.name: cableTestStatusPair0DistanceToFault
cableTestStatusPair0DistanceToFault.description: Distance to fault on wire pair 0 in centimeters. Indicates 0 when no fault is detected or the function is unused.

cableTestStatusPair1State.description: Indicates line termination test results for wire pair 1 (Pins 3/6)

cableTestStatusPair1DistanceToFault.description: Distance to fault on wire pair 1 in centimeters. Indicates 0 when no fault is detected or the function is unused.

cableTestStatusPair2State.name: cableTestStatusPair2State
cableTestStatusPair2State.description: Indicates line termination test results for wire pair 2 (Pins 4/5)

cableTestStatusPair2DistanceToFault.name: cableTestStatusPair2DistanceToFault
cableTestStatusPair2DistanceToFault.description: Distance to fault on wire pair 2 in centimeters. Indicates 0 when no fault is detected or the function is unused.

cableTestStatusPair3State.name: cableTestStatusPair3State
cableTestStatusPair3State.description: Indicates line termination test results for wire pair 3 (Pins 7/8)

cableTestStatusPair3DistanceToFault.name: cableTestStatusPair3DistanceToFault
cableTestStatusPair3DistanceToFault.description: Distance to fault on wire pair 3 in centimeters. Indicates 0 when no fault is detected or the function is unused.
